<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/432009-does-this-book-not-sound-like-an-argument">Does this book not sound like an argument against human freedom?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_432009'><a id="like_count_community_question_432009" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/432009?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F7785194-the-moral-landscape">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/432009-does-this-book-not-sound-like-an-argument">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/432009-does-this-book-not-sound-like-an-argument">See all 4 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/7403320-jeffrey"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1340837134i/7403320._UY100_CR1,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/7403320-jeffrey">Jeffrey</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">No more than any other normative moral system is an argument against human freedom. Normative morality is always about what people should be doing and<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">No more than any other normative moral system is an argument against human freedom. Normative morality is always about what people should be doing and how they should behave themselves. That's just how ethical systems work, otherwise they wouldn't be ethical systems.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

